cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with tasks in graphics and vision, specifically converting shapes into representations with sparse sets of parameters. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new framework for predicting parametric shapes using deep learning, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses distance fields to transition between shape parameters and input data, which suggests that it may also belong to the scientific computing (cs.SI) sub-category.
